<div class="c230_88"> 
<div id="v230.88.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4210 s"> <i>or</i> Psalm</span><span class="H1121 s"> for the sons</span><span class="H7141 s"> of Korah</span><span class="H5329 s">, to the chief Musician</span><span class="H4257 s"> upon Mahalath</span><span class="H6031 s"> Leannoth</span><span class="H4905 s">, Maschil</span><span class="H1968 s"> of Heman</span><span class="H250 s"> the Ezrahite</span><span class="H3068 s">. O LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3444 s"> of my salvation</span><span class="H6817 s">, I have cried</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span><span class="H3915 s"> <i>and</i> night</span> before thee: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (for the sons: or, of the sons) (Maschilâ€¦: or, A Psalm of Heman the Ezrahite, giving instruction)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.88.2"><span class="H8605 s">Let my prayer</span><span class="H935 s"> come</span><span class="H6440 s"> before</span><span class="H5186 s"> thee: incline</span><span class="H241 s"> thine ear</span><span class="H7440 s"> unto my cry</span>;</div> 
<div id="v230.88.3"><span class="H5315 s">For my soul</span><span class="H7646 s"> is full</span><span class="H7451 s"> of troubles</span><span class="H2416 s">: and my life</span><span class="H5060 s"> draweth nigh</span><span class="H7585 s"> unto the grave</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.4"><span class="H2803 s">I am counted</span><span class="H3381 s"> with them that go down</span><span class="H953 s"> into the pit</span><span class="H1397 s">: I am as a man</span><span class="H353 s"> <i>that hath</i> no strength</span>:</div> 
<div id="v230.88.5"><span class="H2670 s">Free</span><span class="H4191 s"> among the dead</span><span class="H2491 s">, like the slain</span><span class="H7901 s"> that lie</span><span class="H6913 s"> in the grave</span><span class="H2142 s">, whom thou rememberest</span><span class="H1504 s"> no more: and they are cut off</span><span class="H3027 s"> from thy hand</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (from: or, by)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.88.6"><span class="H7896 s">Thou hast laid</span><span class="H8482 s"> me in the lowest</span><span class="H953 s"> pit</span><span class="H4285 s">, in darkness</span><span class="H4688 s">, in the deeps</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.7"><span class="H2534 s">Thy wrath</span><span class="H5564 s"> lieth hard</span><span class="H6031 s"> upon me, and thou hast afflicted</span><span class="H4867 s"> <i>me</i> with all thy waves</span><span class="H5542 s">. Selah</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.8"><span class="H7368 s">Thou hast put away</span><span class="H3045 s"> mine acquaintance</span><span class="H7368 s"> far</span><span class="H7896 s"> from me; thou hast made</span><span class="H8441 s"> me an abomination</span><span class="H3607 s"> unto them: <i>I am</i> shut up</span><span class="H3318 s">, and I cannot come forth</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.9"><span class="H5869 s">Mine eye</span><span class="H1669 s"> mourneth</span><span class="H6040 s"> by reason of affliction</span><span class="H3068 s">: LORD</span><span class="H7121 s">, I have called</span><span class="H3117 s"> daily</span><span class="H7849 s"> upon thee, I have stretched out</span><span class="H3709 s"> my hands</span> unto thee.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.10"><span class="H6213 s">Wilt thou shew</span><span class="H6382 s"> wonders</span><span class="H4191 s"> to the dead</span><span class="H7496 s">? shall the dead</span><span class="H6965 s"> arise</span><span class="H3034 s"> <i>and</i> praise</span><span class="H5542 s"> thee? Selah</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.11"><span class="H2617 s">Shall thy lovingkindness</span><span class="H5608 s"> be declared</span><span class="H6913 s"> in the grave</span><span class="H530 s">? <i>or</i> thy faithfulness</span><span class="H11 s"> in destruction</span>?</div> 
<div id="v230.88.12"><span class="H6382 s">Shall thy wonders</span><span class="H3045 s"> be known</span><span class="H2822 s"> in the dark</span><span class="H6666 s">? and thy righteousness</span><span class="H776 s"> in the land</span><span class="H5388 s"> of forgetfulness</span>?</div> 
<div id="v230.88.13"><span class="H7768 s">But unto thee have I cried</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H1242 s">; and in the morning</span><span class="H8605 s"> shall my prayer</span><span class="H6923 s"> prevent</span> thee.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.14"><span class="H3068 s">LORD</span><span class="H2186 s">, why castest thou off</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H5641 s">? <i>why</i> hidest</span><span class="H6440 s"> thou thy face</span> from me?</div> 
<div id="v230.88.15"><span class="H6041 s">I <i>am</i> afflicted</span><span class="H1478 s"> and ready to die</span><span class="H5290 s"> from <i>my</i> youth</span><span class="H5375 s"> up: <i>while</i> I suffer</span><span class="H367 s"> thy terrors</span><span class="H6323 s"> I am distracted</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.16"><span class="H2740 s">Thy fierce wrath</span><span class="H5674 s"> goeth over</span><span class="H1161 s"> me; thy terrors</span><span class="H6789 s"> have cut me off</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.88.17"><span class="H5437 s">They came round about</span><span class="H3117 s"> me daily</span><span class="H4325 s"> like water</span><span class="H5362 s">; they compassed</span><span class="H3162 s"> me about together</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (daily: or, all the day)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.88.18"><span class="H157 s">Lover</span><span class="H7453 s"> and friend</span><span class="H7368 s"> hast thou put far</span><span class="H3045 s"> from me, <i>and</i> mine acquaintance</span><span class="H4285 s"> into darkness</span>.</div></div> 
